	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; 	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0; 	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0; 	mso-style-noshow:yes; 	mso-style-priority:99; 	mso-style-qformat:yes; 	mso-style-parent:\"\"; 	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; 	mso-para-margin-top:0in; 	mso-para-margin-right:0in; 	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt; 	mso-para-margin-left:0in; 	line-height:115%; 	mso-pagination:widow-orphan; 	font-size:11.0pt; 	font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\"; 	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; 	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin; 	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; 	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast; 	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri; 	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;} </style> <![endif]-->  </h1><br /><h1>Welcome to Center for Campus Life!!!!</h1><br />  <p> I am thrilled that you are visiting us on-line, and invite you to take a look through the entire website for important and valuable information.  The Center for Campus Life is here to provide assistance to each of you, as a member of the RIT community, while you seek your own unique way of contributing to or connecting with life in the extended activities&#39; and events&#39; &quot;classroom&quot;; the classroom beyond your academic environments, and designed to support and enhance your student experience. </p>  <p> Through programming design, implementation, and support, our efforts aim to provide opportunities for students to connect with other students, faculty and staff. The programs and related services we coordinate meet a variety of broad and diverse needs.  From helping students to create their own club to sponsoring student led events, from inviting and informing the campus about the active social environment and fraternity and sorority life at RIT to encouraging the pursuit of hobbies related to your own personal interests, the Center seeks to provide something for everyone! </p>  <p> Staff from the Center also manage and coordinate services in our campus&#39; Student Alumni Union.  The SAU is host to a variety of student and staff departments.  Each of these offices is central to creating and maintaining a diverse and healthy campus community.  Feel free to visit the Club Resource Center - located in the RITreat at the SAU, and the SAU Information Desk - in the first floor lobby of the SAU, to learn more about the specific departments and offices in the building, and about how you can connect with events, organizations, and staff members! </p>  <p> My hope is that as you tour this website, you will learn more about the exciting and dynamic community RIT provides for students wishing to be involved at any and all levels!  And, that you will see the enthusiasm and commitment our Campus Life staff has in their ultimate goal of supporting your success.  If you have any questions, or would like to provide feedback about additions and updates to the site, please do not hesitate to contact me.  Again, welcome, and I am so grateful for your visit! </p><br /><br />  <p> Sincerely,<br /><br /> Karey T. Pine,<br /> Director, Center for Campus Life<br /> ktprla@rit.edu   </p>','2010-09-04 20:03:00','cclwww','index','index',''),(14,0,'We all live in a yellow submarine  Or do we? adsfasdfadfazfdaqfdszsdfdsaf','2010-09-03 17:10:27','cclwww','test','about','Test Content'),(15,0,'<p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <br /><br /><br /><br />','2007-07-20 09:49:15','1','about','departments','Departments'),(17,0,'The Club Review Board (CRB) is the student led advisory board that oversees all services, policies, and procedures that relate to Student Government&#39;s recognized clubs. The CRB is comprised of student representatives from a variety of SG clubs, is organized by the SG appointed CRB Chair and is advised by the Assistant Director of Campus Life Programs. The CRB meets on a weekly basis to discuss and make decisions regarding club issues.<br /><br /> Some areas that the CRB has responsibility for include: the SG Club Recognition process, allocation of Club Space, Club Meeting agendas and training topics, the Budget Allocation process, and many other issues as they arise throughout the year. The Club Review Board provides an opportunity for the interests and concerns of SG&#39;s clubs to be voiced and addressed in a positive and productive manner.<br /><br /> The Club Review Board is an important piece of Student Government&#39;s role in RIT&#39;s shared governance. In addition, it is an excellent leadership opportunity. CRB members gain valuable skills in teamwork, decision-making, and critical thinking, while working to improve campus life at RIT.<br /><br />  If you would like to become involved in the Club Review Board, please contact <a href=\"../../..//\" title=\"RIT Student Government\"></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.sg.rit.edu\" title=\"RIT Student Government\">Student Government</a></strong> or the <br /><strong><a href=\"../main/about/profstaff\" title=\"Building Student Participation!\">Center for Campus Life</a></strong>. We encourage participation from SG&#39;s clubs. New members are always welcome.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />','2009-08-20 09:39:45','1','clubs','reviewboard','Club Review Board'),(18,0,'<p>Currently there are approximately 205 active clubs, 11 Major Student Organizations, and 30 Greek Organizations on campus. RIT welcomes and embraces all of its unique, student operated clubs and organizations. <br /><br /> Do you have an interest or hobby? <br />Look through the <a href=\"Find%20a%20club%21\"></a><strong><a href=\"clubs/all\" title=\"Clubs and Organizations\">clubs and organizations</a></strong> at RIT.<br /> You may find a club that shares your interest. <br /><br /> Can&#39;t find a club that you want to join? <br />Find out <strong><a href=\"clubs/howto\" title=\"So you want to form a club?\">how to form a new club</a></strong>.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Club Day <br /><br /></strong>Want to meet members from a club you would like to join? <br />Club Days are 10am-4pm in the Student Alumni Union Lobby.<br /><br />Club Day Dates:</p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'\">September 24, 2010</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'\">October 22, 2010</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'\">December 17, 2010</span></p></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'\">January 27, 2011 </span></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'\">April 29, 2011</span></p></li></ul><ul><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>  <w:WordDocument>   <w:View>Normal</w:View>   <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>   <w:TrackMoves/>   <w:TrackFormatting/>   <w:PunctuationKerning/>   <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>   <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>   <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>   <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>   <w:DoNotPromoteQF/>   <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>   <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>   <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>   <w:Compatibility>    <w:BreakWrappedTables/>    <w:SnapToGridInCell/>    <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>    <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>    <w:DontGrowAutofit/>    <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark/>    <w:DontVertAlignCellWithSp/>    <w:DontBreakConstrainedForcedTables/>    <w:DontVertAlignInTxbx/>    <w:Word11KerningPairs/>    <w:CachedColBalance/>   </w:Compatibility>   <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplorer4</w:BrowserLevel>   <m:mathPr>    <m:mathFont m:val=\"Cambria Math\"/>    <m:brkBin m:val=\"before\"/>    <m:brkBinSub m:val=\"&#45;-\"/>    <m:smallFrac m:val=\"off\"/>    <m:dispDef/>    <m:lMargin m:val=\"0\"/>    <m:rMargin m:val=\"0\"/>    <m:defJc m:val=\"centerGroup\"/>    <m:wr